{"title_page": "Kaohsiung Jeoutai Technology Basketball Team", "text_new": "{{Basketball team\n| team          = Kaohsiung Jeoutai Technology <br /> \u9ad8\u96c4\u4e5d\u592a\u79d1\u6280\n| color1        = \n| color2        = \n| logo          = KKL Basketball.png\n| pixels        = \n| founded       = 2003\n| league        = [[Super Basketball League|SBL]]\n| history       = \n| arena         = \n| city          = [[Kaohsiung]], [[Taiwan]]\n| colors        = \n| owner         = \n| coach         = {{flagicon|TPE}} Liu Jia-fa\n| championships = \n| titles        = \n| cheerleaders  = \n| dancers       = \n| mascot        = \n}}\n\n'''Kaohsiung Jeoutai Technology Basketball Team''' ({{zh|s=\u9ad8\u96c4\u4e5d\u592a\u79d1\u6280\u7bee\u7403\u961f|t=\u9ad8\u96c4\u4e5d\u592a\u79d1\u6280\u7c43\u7403\u968a|p=G\u0101oxi\u00f3ng Ji\u01d4t\u00e0i K\u0113j\u00ec L\u00e1nqi\u00fa Du\u00ec}}), formerly known as the '''ETTV Antelopes''' ({{zh|s=\u4e1c\u68ee\u7f9a\u7f8a|t=\u6771\u68ee\u7f9a\u7f8a|p=d\u014dng s\u0113n l\u00edng y\u00e1ng}}) and '''Kinmen Kaoliang Liquor Basketball Team''' ({{zh|s=\u91d1\u95e8\u9ad8\u7cb1\u9152\u5382\u7bee\u7403\u961f|t=\u91d1\u9580\u9ad8\u7cb1\u9152\u5ee0\u7c43\u7403\u968a|p=J\u012bnm\u00e9n G\u0101oli\u00e1ng Ji\u01d4ch\u01ceng L\u00e1nqi\u00fa Du\u00ec}} is a semi-professional [[basketball]] team that plays in the [[Super Basketball League]] (SBL), the first-tier basketball league in [[Taiwan]]. In 2008, [[Kinmen Kaoliang Liquor]] took over the team from [[Eastern Broadcasting Company|ETTV]] and adopted the new team name, it is now officially sponsored by Kinmen Kaoliang Liquor.\n\n==SBL regular season records==\n* 2003\u20132004 season: 5th place\n* 2004\u20132005 season: 5th place\n* 2005\u20132006 season: 6th place\n* 2006\u20132007 season: 5th place\n* 2007\u20132008 season: 3rd place\n* 2008\u20132009 season: 5th place\n* 2009\u20132010 season: 6th place\n* 2010\u20132011 season: 7th place\n* 2011\u20132012 season: 5th place\n* 2012\u20132013 season: 6th place\n* 2013\u20132014 season: 6th place\n* 2014\u20132015 season: 6th place\n* 2015\u20132016 season: 7th place\n* 2016\u20132017 season: 6th place\n* 2017\u20132018 season: 3rd place\n* 2018\u20132019 season: 5th place\n\n==Notable coach==\n{|\n|valign=\"top\"|\n* {{flagicon|TPE}} [[Chen Yong-le]] <small>2003\u201304</small>\n* {{flagicon|TPE}} [[Liu Hua-lin]] <small>2004\u201305</small>\n* {{flagicon|TPE}} [[Li Yun-hsiang]] <small>2005\u201306</small>\n* {{flagicon|TPE}} [[Qiu Da-zong]] <small>2006\u201307</small>\n* {{flagicon|TPE}} [[Wu Jian-guo]] <small>2007\u201308</small>\n* {{flagicon|TPE}} [[Luo Tian-jin]] <small>2007\u201311, 2012\u201313</small>\n* {{flagicon|TPE}} [[Hsu Zhi-chao]] <small>2011\u201312, 2015\u201316</small>\n* {{flagicon|TPE}} [[Yang Zhi-hao]] <small>2013\u201314, 2016\u201317</small>\n* {{flagicon|TPE}} [[Wu Jun-xiong]] <small>2014\u201315, 2017\u201319</small>\n* {{flagicon|TPE}} [[Liu Jia-fa]] <small>19\u2013present</small>\n\n|width=\"33\"|&nbsp;\n|valign=\"top\"|\n\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Kinmen]]\n* [[List of basketball leagues]]\n\n{{SBL}}\n\n{{Asia-basketball-team-stub}}\n{{Taiwan-sport-stub}}\n\n[[Category:Basketball teams in Taiwan]]\n[[Category:Super Basketball League]]\n[[Category:Basketball teams established in 2003]]\n", "text_old": "{{Basketball team\n| team          = Kaohsiung Jeoutai Technology <br /> \u9ad8\u96c4\u4e5d\u592a\u79d1\u6280\n| color1        = \n| color2        = \n| logo          = KKL Basketball.png\n| pixels        = \n| founded       = 2003\n| league        = [[Super Basketball League|SBL]]\n| history       = \n| arena         = \n| city          = [[Kaohsiung]], [[Taiwan]]\n| colors        = \n| owner         = \n| coach         = {{flagicon|TPE}} Liu Jia-fa\n| championships = \n| titles        = \n| cheerleaders  = \n| dancers       = \n| mascot        = \n}}\n\n'''Kaohsiung Jeoutai Technology Basketball Team''' ({{zh|s=\u9ad8\u96c4\u4e5d\u592a\u79d1\u6280\u7bee\u7403\u961f|t=\u9ad8\u96c4\u4e5d\u592a\u79d1\u6280\u7c43\u7403\u968a|p=g\u0101o xi\u00f3ng ji\u01d4 t\u00e0i k\u0113 j\u00ec l\u00e1n qi\u00fa du\u00ec}}), formerly known as the '''ETTV Antelopes''' ({{zh|s=\u4e1c\u68ee\u7f9a\u7f8a|t=\u6771\u68ee\u7f9a\u7f8a|p=d\u014dng s\u0113n l\u00edng y\u00e1ng}}) and '''Kinmen Kaoliang Liquor Basketball Team''' ({{zh|s=\u91d1\u95e8\u9ad8\u7cb1\u9152\u5382\u7bee\u7403\u961f|t=\u91d1\u9580\u9ad8\u7cb1\u9152\u5ee0\u7c43\u7403\u968a|p=j\u012bn m\u00e9n g\u0101o li\u00e1ng ji\u01d4 ch\u01ceng l\u00e1n qi\u00fa du\u00ec}} is a semi-professional [[basketball]] team that plays in the [[Super Basketball League]] (SBL), the first-tier basketball league in [[Taiwan]]. In 2008, [[Kinmen Kaoliang Liquor]] took over the team from [[Eastern Broadcasting Company|ETTV]] and adopted the new team name, it is now officially sponsored by Kinmen Kaoliang Liquor.\n\n==SBL regular season records==\n* 2003\u20132004 season: 5th place\n* 2004\u20132005 season: 5th place\n* 2005\u20132006 season: 6th place\n* 2006\u20132007 season: 5th place\n* 2007\u20132008 season: 3rd place\n* 2008\u20132009 season: 5th place\n* 2009\u20132010 season: 6th place\n* 2010\u20132011 season: 7th place\n* 2011\u20132012 season: 5th place\n* 2012\u20132013 season: 6th place\n* 2013\u20132014 season: 6th place\n* 2014\u20132015 season: 6th place\n* 2015\u20132016 season: 7th place\n* 2016\u20132017 season: 6th place\n* 2017\u20132018 season: 3rd place\n* 2018\u20132019 season: 5th place\n\n==Notable coach==\n{|\n|valign=\"top\"|\n* {{flagicon|TPE}} [[Chen Yong-le]] <small>03\u201304</small>\n* {{flagicon|TPE}} [[Liu Hua-lin]] <small>04\u201305</small>\n* {{flagicon|TPE}} [[Li Yun-hsiang]] <small>05\u201306</small>\n* {{flagicon|TPE}} [[Qiu Da-zong]] <small>06\u201307</small>\n* {{flagicon|TPE}} [[Wu Jian-guo]] <small>07\u201308</small>\n* {{flagicon|TPE}} [[Luo Tian-jin]] <small>07\u201311, 12\u201313</small>\n* {{flagicon|TPE}} [[Hsu Zhi-chao]] <small>11\u201312, 15\u201316</small>\n* {{flagicon|TPE}